===Definitions===
{{head|zh|hanzi}}

# [[Confucianism]]; [[Ruism]]
#* {{zh-x|孟子 曰：「逃 ^墨 必 歸 於 ^楊，逃 ^楊 必 歸 於 ^儒。歸，斯 受 之 而 已 矣。今 之 與 ^楊-墨 辯 者，如 追 放 豚，既 入 其 苙，又 從 而 招 之。」|Mencius said, 'Those who are fleeing from the errors of {{w|Mohism}} naturally turn to {{w|Yangism}}, and those who are fleeing from the errors of Yang naturally turn to '''Ruism'''. When they so turn, they should at once and simply be received. Those who nowadays dispute with the followers of Yangism and Mohism do so as if they were pursuing a stray pig, the leg of which, after they have got it to enter the pen, they proceed to tie.'|ref=Mengzi}}
# [[scholar]]; [[learned]] [[person]]
#: {{zh-x|^儒-林 外史|{{w|The Scholars (novel)|Unofficial History of the '''Scholars'''}} {{n-g|(a satirical novel by {{lang|zh|吳敬梓}} {{w|Wu Jingzi}})}}}}
#* {{zh-x|子 謂 ^子-夏 曰：「女{rǔ} 為 君子 儒，無 為 小人 儒。」|The Master said to Zi Xia, "Do you be a '''scholar''' after the style of the superior man, and not after that of the mean man."|ref=Lunyu}}
#* {{zh-x|以 九 兩 系 邦國 之 民：…… 四 曰 儒，以 道 得 民。……。|Use nine working-duos to involve the people of the polities and states: [...] the fourth are called the '''scholars''', who use moral principles to procure people. [...].|ref=Zhouli}}
# [[Confucian]]; [[Ruist]]
#* {{zh-x|通 天、地、人 曰 儒，通 天、地 而 不通 人 曰 伎。|Having a penetrating understanding of Heaven, Earth, and Man is called '''ru (Confucian)'''. Having a penetrating understanding of Heaven and Earth, but not understanding Man, is called "clever."|ref=Fayan}}
# [[weak]]; [[cowardly]]
